.TH "si_dma_vm_write_pte" 9 "si_dma_vm_write_pte" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
si_dma_vm_write_pte \- update PTEs by writing them manually
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" si_dma_vm_write_pte
.BI "(struct amdgpu_ib *ib "  ","
.BI "uint64_t pe "  ","
.BI "uint64_t value "  ","
.BI "unsigned count "  ","
.BI "uint32_t incr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ib" 12
indirect buffer to fill with commands
.IP "pe" 12
addr of the page entry
.IP "value" 12
dst addr to write into pe
.IP "count" 12
number of page entries to update
.IP "incr" 12
increase next addr by incr bytes
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Update PTEs by writing them manually using DMA (SI).
